Fuse data for contigs belonging to the same virus

WGA

wga_table2=merge(x = grouping_table, y=wga_table, by.x="contig_name", by.y="row.names", all.x=FALSE, all.y=TRUE)
dim(wga_table2)
## [1] 50 68
split=split(x = wga_table2, f = wga_table2$virus_name,drop = TRUE)

grouped_data_wga=lapply(X = split, FUN = function(x){
  # compute the mean coverage within the contigs
  numeric_data=apply(X = x[,4:59], MARGIN = 2, mean)
  # add relative informations
  per_cent_identity=mean(x[,"pident"],na.rm=TRUE)
  total_length=sum(x[,"seqs_length"])
  res=as.data.frame(c(numeric_data, as.vector(x[1,c(60:68)])))
  res$pident=per_cent_identity
  res$seqs_length=total_length
  # keep track of the number of contigs merged
  res$ncontigs=dim(x)[1]
  rownames(res)=x$virus_name[1]
  return(res)
})

grouped_data_wga2=do.call(what = rbind.data.frame, grouped_data_wga)
dim(grouped_data_wga2)
## [1]  7 66
write.table(grouped_data_wga2, "../TABLES/wga_grouped_data.txt", row.names = TRUE, col.names = TRUE, quote=FALSE, sep="\t")

head(grouped_data_wga2)

WTA

wta_table2=merge(x = grouping_table, y=wta_table, by.x="contig_name", by.y="row.names", all.x=FALSE, all.y=TRUE)
dim(wta_table2)
## [1] 192  68
split=split(x = wta_table2, f = wta_table2$virus_name,drop = TRUE)

grouped_data_wta=lapply(X = split, FUN = function(x){
  # compute the mean coverage within the contigs
  numeric_data=apply(X = x[,4:59], MARGIN = 2, mean)
  # add relative informations
  per_cent_identity=mean(x[,"pident"],na.rm=TRUE)
  total_length=sum(x[,"seqs_length"])
  res=as.data.frame(c(numeric_data, as.vector(x[1,c(60:68)])))
  res$pident=per_cent_identity
  res$seqs_length=total_length
  
  # define family
  families=unique(x$family)
  families=families[!is.na(families)] # remove NAs
  families=families[grep("Unclass", families, invert=TRUE)] # remove Unclassified

  if (length(families)==0) {
    family="Unclassified"
  }
  if (length(families)>0) {
    family=names(table(families)[table(families)==max(table(families))])[1]
  }
  
  res$family=family
    # keep track of the number of contigs merged
  res$ncontigs=dim(x)[1]
  rownames(res)=x$virus_name[1]
  return(res)
})

grouped_data_wta2=do.call(what = rbind.data.frame, grouped_data_wta)
dim(grouped_data_wta2)
## [1] 46 66
write.table(grouped_data_wta2, "../TABLES/wta_grouped_data.txt", row.names = TRUE, col.names = TRUE, quote=FALSE, sep="\t")

head(grouped_data_wta2)

plot_heatmap=function(mymatrix=wga_cov2_viruses, pdf="test.pdf", name="coverage", colcex=3, rowcex=3, min=0.2, max=1, cluster_rows=TRUE, row_order=NA, cluster_cols=TRUE, col_order=NA, row_title="", show_heatmap_legend=TRUE, show_annotation_name=TRUE, colour_code_viruses=d){

  # dimension of the matrix
  ncols=dim(mymatrix)[2]
  
  # order rows according to something ?
if (cluster_rows){
  cluster_rows=TRUE
  print ("no special row order")
}
if (cluster_rows==FALSE){
  print ("Fixed row order")
  cluster_rows=FALSE
  mymatrix=mymatrix[row_order,]
}
  # extract virus taxonomy info
  taxo=mymatrix[, c((ncols-8):(ncols-1))]

# define the form of names for viruses (rows)
mymatrix$pident=mymatrix$pident*100 #round the percent identity for blastx results
#mymatrix$identity[is.na(mymatrix$identity)]="~100" # to indicate that these are very similar to known viral genomic sequences
# define row labels
#short_names=sub(pattern = "contig_", replacement = "c", rownames(mymatrix))
#labels=paste(rownames(mymatrix), paste0(round(mymatrix$pident,digits = 0), "%"), paste0(mymatrix$seqs_length,"bp"), paste0("n=", mymatrix$ncontigs), sep=" ")
labels=paste(rownames(mymatrix), paste0(round(mymatrix$pident,digits = 0), "%"), paste0(mymatrix$seqs_length,"bp"), sep=" ")

# order cols according to something ?
if (cluster_cols){
  cluster_cols=TRUE
  print ("no special cols order")
}
if (cluster_cols==FALSE){
  print ("Fixed cols order")
  cluster_cols=FALSE
  mymatrix=mymatrix[,col_order]
}


# define colour scheme
col_fun = colorRamp2(c(min, max), c("green", "red"))

# define annotation colors for cols
rows_annotation=strsplit(colnames(mymatrix)[1:(ncols-10)], split = "_", fixed = T)
rows_annotation=do.call(rbind.data.frame,rows_annotation)
names(rows_annotation)=c("species", "location", "year", "season", "libtype")
# to deal with the duplicated sample (D im taken as D. phalerat)
#rows_annotation$libtype[rows_annotation$species=="control"]="WGA"

if (sum(rows_annotation$libtype=="WGAbis")>0){
rows_annotation$libtype[rows_annotation$libtype=="WGAbis"]="WGA"
rows_annotation[rows_annotation$species=="H2O",]=c(NA, NA, NA, NA, "WGA")
}
if (sum(rows_annotation$libtype=="WTAbis")>0){
rows_annotation$libtype[rows_annotation$libtype=="WTAbis"]="WTA"
rows_annotation[rows_annotation$species=="H2O",]=c(NA, NA, NA, NA, "WTA")
}

colnames(mymatrix)[grepl("H2O",colnames(mymatrix))]="neg_control"

rows_annotation$season=as.factor(rows_annotation$season)
#levels(rows_annotation$season)=c(NA,"June", "Sept")
levels(rows_annotation$season)[levels(rows_annotation$season)=="Juin"]="June"
levels(rows_annotation$season)[levels(rows_annotation$season)=="Sept"]="Sept"
#levels(rows_annotation$season)[levels(rows_annotation$season)=="Sept"]="Sept"
#rows_annotation$season=factor(rows_annotation$season)
rows_annotation$year=factor(rows_annotation$year)
rows_annotation$location=factor(rows_annotation$location)
rows_annotation$species=factor(rows_annotation$species)
# reorder columns
rows_annotation=rows_annotation[,c(4,3,2,1)]

# define species colors
cols_ha=c(brewer.pal(3, "Set1"),brewer.pal(12, "Set3"))
col_lb=cols_ha[1]
cols_ha[1]=cols_ha[12]
cols_ha[12]=col_lb
names(cols_ha)=c("A.ruf.tab" , "C.amo"  ,   "D.hyd"  ,   "D.im"    ,  "D.kuntzei" , "D.mel"   ,   "D.pha"  ,    "D.sim" ,    "D.sub"  ,   "D.sub.obs" , "D.suz"  ,   "L.b"    ,   "L.h"    ,   "Pachy"   ,  "Tricho" )

ha = HeatmapAnnotation(df = rows_annotation,
                       col = list(season=c("Sept"="darkgrey", "June"="lightgrey"),
                                  year=c("2011"="lightgrey", "2012"="darkgrey"),
                                  location=c("Ige"="lightgrey", "Gotheron"="darkgrey"),
                                  species=cols_ha),
                       na_col = "white")


# define colour annotation for rows

cols_hb=colour_code_viruses$colour
names(cols_hb)=colour_code_viruses$Family
cols_hb=as.factor(cols_hb)

# reduce to viruses families that are present in the samples
viruses_actually_present=unique(taxo$family)
cols_hb=cols_hb[which(names(cols_hb) %in% viruses_actually_present)]
mymatrix$family=factor(mymatrix$family)

hb= rowAnnotation(family = taxo$family, col= list(family=cols_hb), show_annotation_name = show_annotation_name)


# heatmap
figure=Heatmap(as.matrix(mymatrix[, 1:(ncols-10)]), name = name, # name that appears above the legend scale
                        col=col_fun,  # function for mapping colours to the main data
                        rect_gp = gpar(col="white", lwd=0.4), # add white arround each cell
                        #clustering_distance_rows = function(x, y) 1 - cor(x, y), # define distance for rows
                        #clustering_distance_columns = function(x, y) 1 - cor(x, y) # define distance for cols
                        row_labels = labels,
                        clustering_method_rows = "complete", # define the clustering method
                        clustering_method_columns = "ward.D2", #ward.D2
                        column_names_gp = gpar(fontsize = colcex), # define col label size
                        row_names_gp = gpar(fontsize = rowcex), # define col label size
                        top_annotation = ha,
                        cluster_rows = cluster_rows,
                        cluster_columns= cluster_cols,
                        right_annotation = hb,
                        row_names_max_width = unit(10, "cm"),
                        row_title = row_title,
                        show_heatmap_legend =show_heatmap_legend,
                        row_title_rot = 0
                        ) 

#figure=Heatmap(as.matrix(mymatrix[, 1:(ncols-6)]), name=name, cluster_rows=TRUE, clustering_method_rows = "complete", col=col_fun,rect_gp = gpar(col="white", lwd=0.4), row_labels = labels, cluster_columns = FALSE)

pdf(paste0("../figures/", pdf), width=10, height=10)
draw(figure)
dev.off()

return(figure)
return("done")
}

# replace sequences with no hits or unclassified sequences by "Unclassified"
grouped_data_wta2$family=factor(grouped_data_wta2$family)
levels(grouped_data_wta2$family)
##  [1] "Chuviridae"      "Dicistroviridae" "Flaviviridae"    "Iflaviridae"    
##  [5] "Nodaviridae"     "Partitiviridae"  "Phasmaviridae"   "Phenuiviridae"  
##  [9] "Picornavirales"  "Reoviridae"      "Rhabdoviridae"   "Totiviridae"    
## [13] "Unclassified"
levels(grouped_data_wta2$family)[grep(pattern = "Unclassified", levels(grouped_data_wta2$family))]="Unclassified viruses"
# convert Nas to Unclassified
facna <- addNA(grouped_data_wta2$family)
levels(facna) <- c(levels(grouped_data_wta2$family), "Unclassified viruses")
grouped_data_wta2$family=facna
grouped_data_wta2$family=factor(grouped_data_wta2$family) # drop unused levels

# correct manually a few viruses
levels(grouped_data_wta2$family)=c(levels(grouped_data_wta2$family), "Nidoviridae", "Virga-like")
  
grouped_data_wta2[grep("Reo", rownames(grouped_data_wta2)),]$family="Reoviridae"
grouped_data_wta2[grep("Nido", rownames(grouped_data_wta2)),]$family="Nidoviridae"
grouped_data_wta2[grep("Hepe-Virga_L.b", rownames(grouped_data_wta2)),]$family="Virga-like"
grouped_data_wta2[grep("Virga", rownames(grouped_data_wta2)),]$family="Virga-like"
grouped_data_wta2[grep("Nora", rownames(grouped_data_wta2)),]$family="Picornavirales"
grouped_data_wta2[grep("Partiti-like", rownames(grouped_data_wta2)),]$family="Partitiviridae"

# reorder factors  
# reorder families
virus_fams <- ordered(grouped_data_wta2$family)
grouped_data_wta2$family <- ordered(virus_fams, levels = d$Family)

write.table(grouped_data_wta2, 
            file = "../TABLES/grouped_data_wta2.txt", 
            sep="\t", 
            col.names = TRUE, 
            row.names = TRUE,
            quote = FALSE)
plot_heatmap(mymatrix=grouped_data_wta2, pdf="heatmap_cov_wta2_grouped.pdf", name="contig coverage", rowcex = 7, colour_code_viruses = d)
